description.plain: Timucin Fabian Kwong Wah Aluo (born 25 July 1987), known professionally as Jax Jones, is an English multi-instrumentalist, record producer, songwriter and DJ. He is best known for featuring on Duke Dumont’s 2014 single “I Got U”, peaking to number one on the UK Singles Chart.

songs.full_title: Instruction by Jax Jones (Ft. Demi Lovato & Stefflon Don)
songs.title: Instruction

description.plain:
“Instruction” is released as the third single from Jax Jones’s debut studio album. The samba-infused dance hall anthem is a collaboration with American pop singer, Demi Lovato and British rapper Stefflon Don.

The song is a summer banger with heavy drum assist where Lovato sings about self empowerment.

The cover art of the single follows Jones' theme of using household products, this one being inspired by Sriracha sauce.

The cover art of the single follows Jones' theme of using household products, this one being inspired by Sriracha sauce.

songs.full_title: Breathe by Jax Jones (Ft. Ina Wroldsen)
songs.title: Breathe

description.plain:
“Breathe” is the up-tempo follow up track to the smash hit “Instruction” featuring Demi Lovato & Stefflon Don.

This time, actress-singer Ina Wroldsen lends her vocals to explore the themes of the complexity of a toxic love.

Jax Jones has been criticized for using his unreleased track “This Is Real” featuring Selena Gomez in order to gain traction in his song releases as evidenced below:

https://twitter.com/LifeWithSelG/status/935575249885847552
